# Oracle View API - Production Server Assessment Checklist

## Objective

The purpose of this assessment is to collect all the technical information required to package the Oracle View API as an RPM package, deploy it on the Production RHEL server, register it as a systemd service and integrate it with the existing FCSCMT application.

---

# 1. Operating System

Verify the operating system version and architecture.

```bash
cat /etc/redhat-release
uname -a
uname -m

rpm --version
yum --version
systemctl --version
```

Document:

- RHEL Version
- Architecture
- RPM Version
- systemd Version

---

# 2. Existing Python Runtime

A corporate Python runtime has been identified under

```
/app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15
```

Verify:

```bash
ls -la /app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15

find /app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15 \
-maxdepth 2 \
-type f \
\( -name python3 -o -name python -o -name pip3 -o -name pip \)

```

Check:

```bash
/app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15/bin/python3 --version

/app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15/bin/python3 -m pip --version

/app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15/bin/python3 -m venv --help
```

Determine whether this Python installation belongs to an RPM package.

```bash
rpm -qf /app/M50/m50-python-3.10.15/bin/python3
```

Questions:

- Is Python managed through RPM?
- Can applications use this Python runtime?
- Can virtual environments be created from it?

---

# 3. Application Directory Structure

Inspect the existing M50 filesystem layout.

```bash
ls -ld /app
ls -ld /app/M50

find /app/M50 -maxdepth 2 -type d | sort
```

Verify whether there are standard directories such as

- bin
- conf
- etc
- lib
- logs
- tmp
- packages

Determine the recommended installation directory for the API.

Possible options:

```
/app/M50/api-reporter
```

or

```
/opt/api-reporter
```

---

# 4. Existing FCSCMT Service User

Determine which operating system user is running FCSCMT.

```bash
ps -ef | grep java

ps -ef | grep tomcat
```

Inspect ownership.

```bash
ls -ld /app/M50
ls -ld /app/M50/*
```

Verify

- Service User
- Service Group
- Home Directory

Question:

Should the API run under

- the existing FCSCMT service account

or

- a dedicated service account?

---

# 5. Existing systemd Services

Identify the current application service.

```bash
systemctl list-unit-files | grep -Ei "fcscmt|tomcat|m50"

systemctl status <SERVICE_NAME>

systemctl cat <SERVICE_NAME>
```

Collect

- ExecStart
- User
- Group
- WorkingDirectory
- EnvironmentFile

---

# 6. Existing Configuration Structure

Determine where application configuration files are stored.

```bash
find /app/M50 \
-maxdepth 3 \
-type f \
\( -name "*.properties" \
-o -name "*.conf" \
-o -name "*.env" \)
```

Questions

Where should the Oracle View API configuration be stored?

Examples

```
/app/M50/api-reporter/conf/api-reporter.env
```

or

```
/etc/api-reporter/
```

---

# 7. Existing Logging Structure

Determine where application logs are written.

```bash
find /app/M50 \
-maxdepth 3 \
-type d \
\( -iname log -o -iname logs \)

find /var/log \
-maxdepth 2 \
-type d | grep -Ei "fcscmt|m50|tomcat"
```

Determine

- log directory
- ownership
- permissions

Also verify

```bash
journalctl -u <SERVICE_NAME> -n 20
```

Question

Should the API use

- journalctl only

or

- journalctl + dedicated log file

---

# 8. Port Availability

Verify whether port 8000 is available.

```bash
ss -ltnp | grep 8000

ss -ltnp | grep -E "443|8080|8443"
```

Question

Can the API safely bind to

```
127.0.0.1:8000
```

---

# 9. HTTPS Infrastructure

Determine which component terminates HTTPS.

```bash
ps -ef | grep -Ei "httpd|apache|nginx|tomcat|java"

systemctl status httpd

systemctl status nginx

systemctl status tomcat

ss -ltnp | grep 443
```

Question

Is HTTPS terminated by

- Apache HTTP Server
- Tomcat
- Nginx
- Load Balancer
- API Gateway

---

# 10. TLS Certificate

Verify whether the Oracle View API can reuse the existing FCSCMT certificate.

Questions

- Which certificate is currently used?
- Can the API be exposed as

```
https://fcscmt.company.com/api/reporter
```

using the same certificate?

---

# 11. Oracle Connectivity

Verify that the application server can reach Oracle.

```bash
getent hosts <oracle-host>

nc -vz <oracle-host> 1521
```

Determine whether Oracle Wallet or Instant Client is already used.

```bash
find /app/M50 \
-name tnsnames.ora \
-o -name sqlnet.ora
```

---

# 12. Nexus Configuration

Determine whether the server already uses Nexus.

```bash
yum repolist

grep -R nexus /etc/yum.repos.d
```

Questions

- Existing RPM repository?
- Existing Python (PyPI) repository?
- Existing corporate pip.conf?

---

# 13. Security

Check

```bash
getenforce

sestatus

firewall-cmd --state
```

Determine

- SELinux Mode
- Firewall status

---

# 14. Existing RPM Packages

Inspect existing M50 packages.

```bash
rpm -qa | grep -Ei "m50|fcscmt"
```

Inspect one package.

```bash
rpm -qi <PACKAGE>

rpm -ql <PACKAGE>

rpm -q --scripts <PACKAGE>
```

Questions

- Installation path
- Configuration path
- Service registration
- RPM naming convention

